The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Kwara Command has arrested a widower, Samuel Darisa, 65, for allegedly defiling a 10-year old minor at Agbadam area of llorin. The commandant of the command, Makinde Ayinla, said the suspect was picked up after a tip-off by a concerned neighbour that caught them in the act. The commandant added that the suspect confessed to have committed the crime. He, however, said that the minor consented to the affair and that it was not only once he had canal knowledge of the victim. Ayinla said that the suspect would be taken to court after investigations.(NAN)